a generator spread noxious fumes in a 
12story office building sunday killing one man and forcing eight 
others to seek hospital treatment authorities said 
the natural gaspowered generator was turned on after 
philadelphia electric co switched off power to the germantown 
savings bank building in lower merion township just outside 
philadelphia apparently to allow workmen to make repairs 
authorities said 
the generators exhaust pipe was missing a section allowing 
deadly carbon monoxide to escape into the building authorities 
said 
the victim who carried no identification died at osteopathic 
hospital according to spokeswoman susan soiferman 
the hospital admitted a firefighter for inhalation of toxic 
fumes she said he was listed in guarded condition 
at lankenau hospital doctors treated and released six 
