john sununu wields his clout in washington 
these days but his influence still is felt in the state he governed 
for six years before being tapped as george bushs chief of staff 
new hampshires immediate past governor is seen as a smooth 
operator who does favors for his adopted home state but leaves few 
political fingerprints 
some state republicans express concern that sununu is meddling 
in local politics but most consider his presence in the white 
house to be an asset for the state 
sununu makes certain new hampshires place on the political 
map is not forgotten said gop strategist tom rath 
it was not an accident that the first place outside of 
washington that the president visited was new hampshire rath 
said referring to a bush stopover in manchester not long after he 
became president 
as new hampshires governor sununu sided early with bush in the 
1988 presidential race he helped engineer a bush victory in the 
states earliestinthenation primary and continued the national 
campaign with attacks against democratic nominee michael dukakis 
governor of neighboring massachusetts 
sununus political work continues even now he had a guiding 
role in easing the white houses handsoff policy toward party 
primaries putting the oval office behind candidates such as rep 
bob smith rnh who hopes to replace retiring gop sen gordon 
humphrey 
state gop chairwoman rhona charbonneau wishes sununu had stayed 
out of the primary race between smith and rye lawyer tom christo 
its good to have a friend in the white house rather than a 
foe she said but i truly wish they had kept out of the 
primary i dont believe anybody not even the white house should 
be involved 
sununu whose influence also can be seen in some state races 
brushes off the criticism 
were not trying to pick candidates he says were trying 
to help the process 
his wife nancy hasnt kept silent either she said she 
considered challenging us rep chuck douglas for the gop 
nomination in new hampshires 2nd congressional district because 
she never appreciated his values and his morals 
sununu and his successor in the governors mansion republican 
judd gregg have what insiders consider a civil relationship at 
