when the navy threatened 1000 jobs by canceling a 128 million 
submarine overhaul at the portsmouth naval shipyard maine and new 
hampshire governors and congressional delegations won a pledge by 
the navy to find replacement work 
humphrey credits sununu with making the navy deliver 
when those promises started to filter down the navy 
bureaucracy was sidestepping it so i called sununu and he got them 
to do what they said they would do humphrey recalls 
humphrey said sununu is clearing similar hurdles for a proposal 
the senator is championing to make a wildlife refuge out of some of 
the land to be abandoned when pease air force base closes 
a string of people with new hampshire connections have been 
appointed to federal posts since sununu moved to washington most 
recently wally stickney a sununu friend and associate was 
selected to head the federal emergency management agency 
a highly placed republican who agreed to discuss sununu only if 
not quoted by name said sununu is adept at maintaining a low 
profile in the state 
he hasnt left any fingerprints or left anyone with a story 
that they can tell that sununu sidled up to me and so on 
seabrook the republican said falls into that category sununu 
champion of the nuclear power plant when he was governor didnt 
just go to the nuclear regulatory commission and say give them 
the license the source said 
hes been very cautious but seabrook got the license didnt 
it he made sure his feelings on the topic were well known in the 
appropriate places 
sununu plays down his role in the licensing of seabrook 
i was a patient man he said recently i knew the right 
thing would happen 
