the constitutional article at the core 
of east germanys stunning consideration sunday to immediately join 
west germany has existed since the founding of separate german 
states in 1949 
article 23 was always viewed as a means toward eventual 
reunification of the german people although that seemed only a 
remote possibility more than 40 years ago 
in east berlin on sunday the east german parliament 
overwhelmingly voted to consider the provision but then put off a 
vote 
